Plymouth themes for Arch



To active Plymouth learn howto https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Plymouth

* HOW TO INSTALL *

Copy the theme folder arch-logo to: /usr/share/plymouth/themes/

The available themes can be listed with:
# plymouth-set-default-theme --list

Update your plymouth configuration (as root):
# plymouth-set-default-theme <selected_theme>

Configure it as your default plymouth theme with (as root):
# mkinitcpio -p kernel26


* CREDITS *

arch-logo
Arch adaptation of the debian-logo and ubuntu-logo theme, all credits goes to Alberto Milone for the original coding.

